      • readFireSeasonData

        public static void readFireSeasonData(java.io.BufferedReader fin)
                               throws SimpplleError
        reads fire season data from fire season data file. this is a comma separated value file (csv) file, has method to directly read spring, summer, fall and winter fire data, plus can calculate winter data if only spring, summer, and fall present. marks System Knowledge fire season data not changed
        Parameters:
        fin - the buffered reader
        Throws:
        SimpplleError - catches parseerror, IOException, and Exception for invalid number of items, read problems, or missing data respectively. SimpplleError will be caught in gui,
